place.name: TATTERFORD
place.gazetteerText: TATTERFORD, a parish in Walsingham district, Norfolk; 3½ miles W by S of Fakenham r. station-Post town, Raynham, under Br and on. Acres, 959. Real property, £1,455. Pop., 70. Houses, 14. The living is a rectory, united with Tattersett, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £685.* Patron, J. S. Chad, Esq. The church was rebuilt in 1862. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
